# Build a scoring rubric

## Inputs

- Question: `{{ vars.question }}`
- Session context: {% if vars.context %}`{{ vars.context }}`{% else %}_(none provided)_{% endif %}

## Task

Produce 3-8 weighted scoring dimensions for THIS question.
Use the session context to bias weights toward what
actually matters here — not a generic checklist.

For each dimension supply: `name`, `description`, `weight`
(1-10 scalar), `what_better_means`, `what_worse_means`.
Restate the question in `question_restated` and explain
your weighting choices in `weighting_rationale`.

## Output

```bash
LOOM=~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/scripts/loom.sh
WD={{ run.workdir }}

$LOOM output init "$WD" --task rubric

$LOOM output add "$WD" --task rubric \
    --set 'question_restated=...' \
    --set 'dimensions.0.name=correctness' \
    --set 'dimensions.0.description=...' \
    --set 'dimensions.0.weight=4' \
    --set 'dimensions.0.what_better_means=...' \
    --set 'dimensions.0.what_worse_means=...' \
    --set 'dimensions.1.name=...' \
    ...
    --set 'weighting_rationale=...'
```

Path syntax: dotted paths only. `dimensions.0.name` sets
the first array entry's `name`; `dimensions.1.name`
appends another. Numeric segments index into arrays.
